Guyana</link></group>
</political_system>
</colony>
</monarchy>
</social_group>
</body>
</autocracy>
 in 1934). He began his performing career as a <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../352/4542352.xml">
folk singer</link> in <region wordnetid="108630985" confidence="0.8">
<administrative_district wordnetid="108491826" confidence="0.8">
<location wordnetid="100027167" confidence="0.8">
<district wordnetid="108552138" confidence="0.8">
<country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.8">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../131/8210131.xml">
New York</link></country>
</district>
</location>
</administrative_district>
</region>
. In 1962 he came to <village wordnetid="108672738" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../867/17867.xml">
London</link></village>
 and worked with Pearl Connor's Negro Theatre Workshop initially as a musician and later as an <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../753/753.xml">
actor</link>. His theatre career saw him perform on the major stages in London such as the <theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../775/167775.xml">
Royal National Theatre</link></theater>
, the <theater wordnetid="104417809" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../473/1306473.xml">
Donmar Warehouse</link></theater>
 and <building wordnetid="102913152" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../802/728802.xml">
Bristol Old Vic</link></building>
.<p>

